detaileddescription.para:
These numbers fit within int32_t: you can test for a attribute being available for a geometric object by writing, for example: if (attribute_get_table[EMB_TEXT_SINGLE] & EMB_AREA) {
    // Code that runs if text objects can have a known area.
}

These numbers fit within int32_t: you can test for a attribute being user alterable by a geometric object by writing, for example: if (attribute_set_table[EMB_TEXT_SINGLE] & EMB_AREA) {
    // Code that runs if text objects can have their area set.
}
